                    <msContents>
                        <summary>Tārika Walda, ʿAmid Ḥassabāt, chronological texts</summary>
                        <msItem xml:id="ms_i1">
                            <locus from="2ra" to="3rc"/>
                            <title>Table of contents of Philoxenus of Mabbog</title>
                            <note>List of 176 chapters without relation to the following content, apparently an incomplete table of contents of
                                <ref type="work" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT1399Filkes">Filkǝsyos</ref>.</note>
                            <incipit xml:lang="gez">አርእስተ፡ ዝንቱ፡ መጽሐፍ። ፩፡ በእንተ፡ ብሕቱና፡ እማኅበር፡ ዘከመ፡ ይኄይስ። ፪፡ በእንተ፡ አስብ፡ መጠነ፡ ሕሊና። ፫፡ በከመ፡
                                ይኄይስ፡ ምንኵስና፡ እምሕዝባዊያን።</incipit>
                            <explicit xml:lang="gez">፻፸፭፡ ንስማዕኬ፡ መንከረ፡ በእንተ፡ እንጦንዮስ። ፻፸፮፡ <cb n="3rc"/> በእንተ፡ ብርሃን።</explicit>
                        </msItem>
                        <msItem xml:id="ms_i2">
                            <locus from="4ra" to="84vc"/>
                            <title type="incomplete" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT6936TarWaAmidBeta">Tārika Walda ʾAmid (β-recension)</title>
                            <note>Covering the time from the creation until Emperor Tiberius.</note>
                            <incipit xml:lang="gez">በስመ፡ እግዚአብሔር፡ መሓሪ፡ ወመስተሣህል፡ እትረዳእ፡ ወእዌጥን፡ ጽሕፈተ፡ ታሪክ፡ ዘውእቱ፡ ዜናሆሙ፡ ለአበው፡ ቀደምት፡
                                ወሐሳበ፡ ኆልቈ፡ መዋዕሊሆሙ፡ ለነገሥት፡ እምአዳም፡ እስከ፡ ተፍጻሜቶሙ፡ ለእስራኤል፡ ወለአሕዛብ፡ 
                                <supplied reason="omitted">ዘ</supplied>አስተጋብኦ፡ አብ፡ ክቡር፡ ወትሩፍ፡ ክርስቶሳዊ፡ ጊዮርጊስ፡ ወልደ፡ ዓሚድ፡ ዘብሔረ፡ ግብጽ። 
                                ወሰላመ፡ እግዚአብሔር፡ የሀሉ፡ ላዕለ፡ ገብሩ፡ ንጉሥነ፡ ኢያሱ፡ ለዓለመ፡ ዓለም፡ አሜን።</incipit>
                            <explicit xml:lang="gez">ወይቤ፡ ካዕበ፡ በእንቲአሁ፡ እስመ፡ ውእቱ፡ ቃለ፡ እዋጺ፡ ዘይጸርሖ፡ በገዳም፡ ወይብል፡ እስተጸልው፡ ወጺሑእ፡ ፍኖቶ፡
                                ለእግዚአብሔር፡ ወዓርዩ፡ መጽያሕቶ።</explicit>
                        </msItem>
                        <msItem xml:id="ms_i3">
                            <locus from="86ra" to="100va"/>
                            <title>Ḥassāba ḥǝggu la-ʾƎgziʾabǝḥer</title>
                            <note>A kind of eternal calendar, which calculates <foreign xml:lang="gez">ṭǝntewon</foreign>,
                                <foreign xml:lang="gez">maṭqǝʿ</foreign>, <foreign xml:lang="gez">ʾabaqte</foreign>, the beginning of the
                                fast of Niniveh and <foreign xml:lang="gez">ṣom</foreign>,
                                the day of Jewish Pascha, the Christian Easter and Pentecost according to the weekday of the first day of the year 
                                (cf. <ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/#Tanasee34">Ṭānāsee 34, ff. 100ra‒104rb</ref>). Some events from Ethiopian 
                                history are mentioned at times partly in form of later additions, e.g. <foreign xml:lang="gez">ወበዝየ፡ ሞተ፡ አቃቤ፡ ሰዓት፡
                                <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS14938Abranyos">አብራንዮስ።</persName></foreign>, who is possibly the mamhǝr of 
                                Kǝbrān, promoted to the rank of the ʾaqābe saʿāt.</note>
                            <incipit xml:lang="gez">በስመ፡ አብ፡ <gap reason="ellipsis"/> ናሁ፡ ጸሐፍነ፡ በረድኤተ፡ እግዚአብሔር፡ ፈጣሪ፡ ሕያው፡ ተናጋሪ፡ ከሃሊ፡ ወገባሪ፡
                                ሐሳበ፡ ሕጉ፡ ለእግዚአብሔር፡ ዘተሠርዐ፡ በአበው፡ ቀደምት፡ ክቡራን፡ ወነበያት፡ ቅዱሳን፡ ወሐዋርያት፡ ንጹሓን፡</incipit>
                        </msItem>
